This is similar to the situation of Yakov Sverdlov, he was an Old Bolshevik who had power equal to Lenin, Trotsky, and Stalin and was actually the real head of state, while his brother Zinovy Peshkov (who was ADOPTED BY MAXIM GORKY) was a Brigadier general in the French military.

Sverdlov is forgotten because he died in 1919 (unclear if eliminated or naturally), but he was a very scary guy, unlike Stalin who just LARPed about a criminal past Sverdlov was an actual dangerous criminal. Zinovy Peshkov was also ambassador to Japan, met with Chiang Kai-shek...

Sverdlov's French general brother was also involved with Churchill's cousin Clare Sheridan and Sverdlov's own wife was related to Old Believer families in Russia like the Morozovs. It's all a small closed club. Everyone knows each other there.
To be honest that's probably why he died in the first place
He's just taking a quick exotic vacation as a break from dismantling Russia, it's like going to a Southern beach resort to him

This Andro post actually made me really regret not trying at our Geography Olympiad back when I was in high school. Been going through the Nationals questions from the final rounds and it's very doable. I feel like I could have won it if I tryharded and studied for it back then.

I actually took first place in our Literature Olympiad the one year when I decided to participate, but back then I only cared about playing League and lifting weights at the gym every day, if I was less lazy I should have tried preparing for the chemistry Olympiad too.
